@roadrunnerside8
Supposed to contain malicious software, as will any of the toolkits for CEH.

If you want to ensure the safety of your PC, run these in a VM.  You should never play around with software of this nature on your day-to-day PC, as it is not hard to accidentally infect yourself with malicious software if you do not know what you are doing.  

These toolkits contain anti-AV software, trojans, exploits, etc. and should be EXPECTED to set off anti-virus software.
